news.title: Home prices in Hong Kong drop 2.3% in August 2022
news.para: The drop in home prices in one of the world's most unaffordable housing markets last month followed a revised 1.44% decline in July.

news.title: Sunac China seeks to extend payment for $558.35 million bond for the third time: Sources
news.para: After the adjustments, Sunac will not pay the two remaining amortization payments scheduled for this year, and the last instalment will be delayed to March 31, 2024 from Sept 30, 2023, the sources said.

news.title: Orissa HC upholds ban on registering house sale deeds
news.para: The HC was hearing a PIL challenging the validity of Odisha Apartment Ownership (Amendment) Rules-2021 on the ground that it is contrary to provisions of the RERA Act-2016, which mandates transfer of common areas in favour of the association of apartment owners.

news.title: Bengaluru: BBMP carries out technical survey to save houses constructed on drain
news.para: The Palike had recently razed homes built by middle-class citizens as well as tin sheds sitting on drains. It had said homes in upscale layouts would also be dealt with same rigour.

news.title: Ambuja Cements pledges 50% share in ACC as collateral for loans
news.para: Adani has acquired the two firms -- Ambuja and ACC -- through a Mauritius-based SPV Endeavour Trade and Investment Ltd (ETIL), which is owned by Xcent Trade and Investment Ltd (XTIL).

news.title: China real estate shares, bonds slump on report of CIFI Holdings default
news.para: Hong Kong-listed shares of CIFI Holdings tumbled 26% in morning trading to a record low, after credit intelligence provider Reorg reported that the Chinese developer had missed payment on certain non-standard debt.

news.title: Bengaluru: Seven months on, third-party audit of Kempegowda Layout meanders
news.para: While the agency picked on February 15 to do the audit walked out as it was irked by the differences between the tender amount and payments made, the one that took over the exercise in July-end is yet to submit its report.

news.title: Gurugram: 95% guesthouses illegal, most in licensed colonies, says survey
news.para: The department of town and country planning (DTCP) has, meanwhile, completed the survey of over 2,200 guesthouses operational within the city limits.

news.title: Case against 27 builders in Thane for fabricating documents to obtain RERA registration
news.para: ​The accused developers had allegedly cheated home buyers from 27 villages and the Kalyan Dombivli Municipal Corporation (KDMC) as part of a racket, an official from Manpada police station said.

news.title: Secunderabad cantonment realty assets in ceding list pegged at Rs 20,000 crore
news.para: ​This includes properties owned by Cantonment Board and public spaces dotting SCB-controlled area, said officials, who worked on collating this data — keeping with ministry of defence’s (MoD) excision guidelines.

news.title: H-RERA dismisses plea seeking revocation of Supertech Araville's registration certificate
news.para: The RERA bench headed by its chairman, KK Khandelwal and the three members dismissed the complainant's plea after detailed arguments and scrutiny of documents in the full quorum view.

news.title: Rajasthan government waives 'lease money' of flats sold to MLAs
news.para: These flats were already sold to the MLAs at half the cost during the Covid-19 time. Now the urban development and housing (UDH) minister has waived the lease money. The move will cause a Rs 4 crore loss to the state exchequer, said sources.

news.title: About 800 street lamps in Pune cantonment board areas defunct, finds study
news.para: An internal survey by the electrical engineering section of the PCB revealed that about 20% (800) of the total 4,000 street pole lights in the area are not functional owing to a lack of maintenance.

news.title: Put on notice those behind illegal constructions: Bombay HC
news.para: Taking a tough stand against unauthorised constructions, the Bombay high court on Monday said those responsible for them must “be put on notice”. It gave the direction while hearing a PIL that alleged a floor space index (FSI) scam in Navi Mumbai.

news.title: Government waives fees on 4,000 houses under BSUP scheme in Kalyan-Dombivli
news.para: This will help the KDMC to allot 4,000 houses to the beneficiaries free of charge, Kalyan Lok Sabha MP Shirkant Shinde said on Tuesday while adressing media.
